VARIABLE BASICS 

- A variable is a named memory locations that store a value
- A variable has multible parts

  Ex: 
      int x; // type and name declaration 
      x = 1; // value assignment 
      
- The types tells the compiler what type of data you are using
   ~ Different types uses differnt amounts of bytes 
- The name is what you call when you want to use it in statements 
- The value is the meaningful data, that will be used in the program 
- The equal sign is the NOT an equal sign in this context
  ~ It means x has been assigned the value of 1
  
  
      
